<h3 local-id=3D"54c071158b33" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Stage3:hybridcloneretrieval,reranking,andexplanation"><span clas=
s=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"e94eccef-6388-48a2-8560-80cc62774ea=
4">Stage 3: hybrid clone retrieval, reranking, and explanation</span></h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"821f4e4c4c2e" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Input:.3">Input:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"84cd69fe8a7d">
<li local-id=3D"151c23d1360a">
<p local-id=3D"5be43d25368f">Stage 1 <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" =
data-ref=3D"1de8c400-dd3f-4480-be4a-27a4f68f8d1a">semantic metadata</span><=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"099ccc9399c9">
<p local-id=3D"0a67c3c07935">Stage 1 lexical and structural features</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"1a1d6bcbdf6b">
<p local-id=3D"3562d3cc902c">Stage 2 embeddings</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"71a087cabe6a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Output:.3"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"668=
7b9cc-b397-424c-904b-7b43b180d2e9">Output</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"6fcdf7b269f5">
<li local-id=3D"9f27aa9e1a69">
<p local-id=3D"dd7fed9b2ef0"><code>symbol_clone_edges.relation_kind</code><=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"efa1e36944e7">
<p local-id=3D"c8d0e6ba45c4"><code>symbol_clone_edges.score</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f0421877d065">
<p local-id=3D"22232bbe3240"><code>symbol_clone_edges.semantic_score</code>=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d3e1c8678ce2">
<p local-id=3D"d9269a53821b"><code>symbol_clone_edges.lexical_score</code><=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d58583d76a43">
<p local-id=3D"740632b204f5"><code>symbol_clone_edges.structural_score</cod=
e></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"af39c3cb03ef">
<p local-id=3D"b8b2eb0ea9a4"><code>symbol_clone_edges.explanation_json</cod=
e></p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"6c65c0bb21d2" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Purpose:.3">Purpose:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"2baf11a57657">
<li local-id=3D"5ae4939d3d85">
<p local-id=3D"71f9b9cd935b">convert raw summaries and vectors into a <span=
 class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"a1c491e1-8839-4955-802f-8955e6=
febfd9">product feature developers can query</span></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aa6a67bb4cb8">
<p local-id=3D"45cb17586316"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"a78068ed-7b6d-4b47-adf8-a930bc77bf16">combine semantic, lexical, and st=
ructural retrieval instead of trusting embeddings alone</span></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7890514f6a22">
<p local-id=3D"9b5e9417d585"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"73674483-62f2-403e-bf21-dd08ad026255">distinguish exact duplicates from=
 semantic neighbours</span></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c4a7232b9ec2">
<p local-id=3D"336572305935"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"9c4f67e8-a9be-4a58-84f9-0565995270c3">identify divergence and extractio=
n candidates</span></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c85e2486b061">
<p local-id=3D"aa13f3c03417"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"4ad92454-d8b4-4377-9ba1-b1b41ab93ec7">explain why two artefacts were ma=
tched</span></p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"015fb5b2f00d" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Retrievalmodel:"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"0ed72213-4dec-47db-9d19-912d2a078363">Retrieval model</span>:</h4>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"9af9a29d1b2c">
<li local-id=3D"8db99a30b3cf">
<p local-id=3D"aa8cdd495fba">generate candidates from semantic nearest neig=
hbours</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"52580635b308">
<p local-id=3D"6b8e124022bd">generate candidates from lexical similarity</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"a99efdb72d12">
<p local-id=3D"f5a9dc35fc0b"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"7af0d71b-2ca3-41b9-bfad-c4b2d314beb7">merge and rerank them</span></p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"96c7af38ec18">
<p local-id=3D"967a7b0974f2"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"02b6e27c-ede5-4d47-b341-0ac3e21204de">compute </span><code><span class=
=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"02b6e27c-ede5-4d47-b341-0ac3e21204de=
">semantic_score</span></code><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-re=
f=3D"02b6e27c-ede5-4d47-b341-0ac3e21204de">, </span><code><span class=3D"in=
line-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"02b6e27c-ede5-4d47-b341-0ac3e21204de">lexi=
cal_score</span></code><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"02=
b6e27c-ede5-4d47-b341-0ac3e21204de">, and </span><code><span class=3D"inlin=
e-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"02b6e27c-ede5-4d47-b341-0ac3e21204de">structu=
ral_score</span></code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0bf96f1f389e">
<p local-id=3D"03762f1416ab">combine them into a final score and relation k=
ind</p></li>
</ol>
<h4 local-id=3D"ac2d5a12962a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Importantdistinction:.1">Important distinction:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"7cd5e37e5ac6">
<li local-id=3D"09ef83115f0d">
<p local-id=3D"f0ca89412888">the pre-stage identifies symbols and their str=
ucture</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8ebd1ecbb309">
<p local-id=3D"f98f70c3424f">Stage 1 tells you what a symbol does and extra=
cts non-vector retrieval features</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b82398f865f">
<p local-id=3D"fbc77d548d99">Stage 2 lets you find <span class=3D"inline-co=
mment-marker" data-ref=3D"42499de9-1b3b-425f-a06f-1d351cc4a927">nearby mean=
ing in vector space</span></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a63fdd56f4a9">
<p local-id=3D"424ce582d54f">Stage 3 decides which neighbours are actually =
useful clones/patterns and explains the match</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2cd5c9c0c543">Without Stage 3, Bitloops has metadata and vec=
tors but not a reliable semantic clone capability.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"34da213e7241" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Generalrule:incrementalindexing">General rule: incremental index=
ing</h2>
<p local-id=3D"645ce175df3e"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"75771fde-8e3b-4741-934b-1c1dd9a34e09">Incremental indexing</span> is no=
t a separate stage. It is a recomputation policy that applies across the wh=
ole pipeline. Do not re-embed the whole repository every time.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"8c1f4cf9f67c" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Recommendedflow"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"2f642893-3efb-40fc-a824-e857e0f431de">Recommended flow</span></h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"447da6ecf21e">
<li local-id=3D"0d019e76b24c">
<p local-id=3D"4f03751a07b8">Resolve target commit_sha.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"69a4deac0d7d">
<p local-id=3D"d555cc498bfb">Use file_state to enumerate blobs in that snap=
shot.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"12809c136ca5">
<p local-id=3D"f566a6a38b83">Join to artefacts.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"319a0a5a8497">
<p local-id=3D"01931687f9f8">Skip symbols whose embedding_input_hash alread=
y exists for the same provider/model.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0fbfb60af1ea">
<p local-id=3D"058a4568fe37">Recompute only changed symbols.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f1d18962b39e">
<p local-id=3D"6d4d5bb57d29">Recompute clone edges only for changed symbols=
 plus their local neighbourhood.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"94e75ebef30e">This keeps the cost acceptable.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"c492096ce7dc" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Examples:"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"439=
e823e-384f-4e04-a0c9-5ce102e79d58">Examples</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"ea33c5b82ed1">
<li local-id=3D"85be3758c9c5">
<p local-id=3D"96a5ea755f6a">if the file changed but a symbol's normalized =
content did not, do not regenerate semantics or embeddings for that symbol<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"db0a419ab984">
<p local-id=3D"d3ed6e90472c">if the summary prompt changed, rerun Stage 1 a=
nd possibly Stage 2 if the embedding input includes the summary</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6f854b1ed2cb">
<p local-id=3D"90e68a2adb4e">if the embedding model changed, rerun Stage 2 =
and the affected Stage 3 clone scoring</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"453b4ca191b0" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Embeddingstrategyoptions">Embedding strategy options</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"b34b54aa25e8" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-OptionA:Bitloops-manageddefault">Option A: <span class=3D"inline=
-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"0b829b4f-5091-4278-89d4-c9ef3a44b69b">Bitloops=
-managed default</span></h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"bec18558d0b1" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Bestfor:"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"f26d=
f218-215a-48e0-8a43-ef014fd67a89">Best for</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"7b59651e4027">
<li local-id=3D"b0e03e342f65">
<p local-id=3D"018e803cba4e">fastest delivery</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f3afd9618e5f">
<p local-id=3D"2ac833859c58">simplest UX</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fcd38036be53">
<p local-id=3D"9ea29598417d">consistent dimensions and quality</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"e41686bb497d" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Pros:"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"3831ca7=
1-26ee-4407-886e-84acc91c6a64">Pros</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"b82575820987">
<li local-id=3D"a19ae80be0cf">
<p local-id=3D"f4e6ed10d1f3">one model family to validate</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e9d6114d5a0f">
<p local-id=3D"1eff72634218">easier score calibration</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a8d965892ebf">
<p local-id=3D"389406a92e99">easier support/debugging</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e9303da78e88">
<p local-id=3D"b95ef8de5eab">predictable storage/index shape</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"0ce563cba025" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Cons:"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"42d0b9e=
4-c51f-4e91-8a91-cdf9ad074d92">Cons</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"2b13bb73eb23">
<li local-id=3D"6542331fc076">
<p local-id=3D"6eaf50b4e00d">less flexible for enterprise/privacy requireme=
nts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aab4383c93db">
<p local-id=3D"6a4e7b7d839a">ties quality and cost to one default provider<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2a94d05fa6f3">
<p local-id=3D"6a6abb04a8d1">users cannot optimize for a specific language/=
domain</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"8b20b44e3be0" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-OptionB:user-selectedhostedprovider"><span class=3D"inline-comme=
nt-marker" data-ref=3D"f091790a-18bb-4508-95ba-6a3679848816">Option B</span=
>: <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"070ab13f-d4e3-400a-9e8=
1-24768ed8f251">user-selected hosted provide</span>r</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"e1ef3bea7482" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Bestfor:.1">Best for:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"2b3a379dbd73">
<li local-id=3D"c653ee201838">
<p local-id=3D"c13e8ee2ab1a">teams already standardized on OpenAI/Anthropic=
/Voyage/Cohere/etc.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"82cbb76255d1">
<p local-id=3D"f4c50594c44a">users who want better retrieval quality than a=
 default local setup</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"4d2d2b70b7b9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Pros:.1">Pros:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"18f60e00030b">
<li local-id=3D"04c8f313fe01">
<p local-id=3D"b3d3a26bfb88">better model choice</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"762ab74db175">
<p local-id=3D"35349e25c5ab">potentially stronger multilingual/code retriev=
al</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b20f402cc20d">
<p local-id=3D"e9df59ef30d9">can separate summarization model from embeddin=
g model</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"2f85aa3b1bef" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Cons:.1">Cons:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"e58e78a5a349">
<li local-id=3D"13e9da567ebb">
<p local-id=3D"f87d4ef9aa76">more config surface</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b9620c7a7a0e">
<p local-id=3D"7c75bde472e2">score comparability becomes model-specific</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"6cc4aed77fa4">
<p local-id=3D"c3935e2c3121">harder operational support</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"40279de25fd7">
<p local-id=3D"17d3e3841eef">dimensions and pricing vary across providers</=
p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"cccef6b201e1" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-OptionC:Localmodels(ollama/llama.cpp/mlx-lm)">Option C: Local mo=
dels (ollama/llama.cpp/mlx-lm)</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"9259c449eda1" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Bestfor:.2">Best for:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"71c1a6a6434d">
<li local-id=3D"157fb55161ca">
<p local-id=3D"ad936581e034">offline/dev mode</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fe38383c0989">
<p local-id=3D"247c565260db">private codebases where external APIs are bloc=
ked</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"edd07f85e8b9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Pros:.2">Pros:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"5ca59a1ceeca">
<li local-id=3D"7af23ba52da8">
<p local-id=3D"4c88f98a3a34">strong privacy story</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ddff289cae7f">
<p local-id=3D"8dd92eca6fa6">no per-call API cost</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b8e188a320c7">
<p local-id=3D"17779b024e5f">works in air-gapped environments</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"d30d6c782239" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Cons:.2">Cons:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"f30f2b81131a">
<li local-id=3D"89b87988428b">
<p local-id=3D"10731e686b99">weaker embedding quality on average unless car=
efully tuned</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"866a55a236bd">
<p local-id=3D"91ce4c4a8384">higher local CPU/GPU cost</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6f010efb5e30">
<p local-id=3D"52001aa8053c">inconsistent throughput across developer machi=
nes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9e6a43113f69">
<p local-id=3D"6aaf09fe8a4c">harder to guarantee stable ranking quality</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"7026e8dea7df" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Recommendationonproviderstrategy">Recommendation on provider str=
ategy</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"24dc9f5eacb2">
<li local-id=3D"3feb54e6f402">
<p local-id=3D"99092371ffb4"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"b903741c-1916-4a04-9a45-35da183bf1d1">Option B for now.</span></p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"88434e0a21c4" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Artefactsusefulforsemanticcloneretrieval">Artefacts useful for s=
emantic clone retrieval</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2fcee3772e4e">For the MVP, only embed artefacts that are sta=
ble, common, and useful units for semantic clone retrieval.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c63bd340545c"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"964bc6cb-8cc4-4801-b7aa-5e4bc4e00131">Recommended MVP</span> artefacts:=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"017b0a4ee5d5">
<li local-id=3D"6a8db622071b">
<p local-id=3D"1d4d36159bae"><code>file</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1744801aa249">
<p local-id=3D"889a5c6fed59"><code>module</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e16e6cdecadf">
<p local-id=3D"82bced68388d"><code>function</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5f5318c1c715">
<p local-id=3D"8992d46f8b2c"><code>method</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"14378827d5a7">
<p local-id=3D"2d69e819c989"><code>class</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1de2fbb7731c">
<p local-id=3D"8d97197bd512"><code>interface</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"46c714cd3923">
<p local-id=3D"e53d8c9083e6"><code>enum</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a53f7d6f173">
<p local-id=3D"70bea47a2736"><code>constructor</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"592916b56e02">
<p local-id=3D"053ddb15641d"><code>test</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"60bde9dbcda1">Why these are enough for the MVP:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"0e601e909c38">
<li local-id=3D"567d7f89b6cf">
<p local-id=3D"ac3f5e667d40">they <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" dat=
a-ref=3D"a7fd08ab-aebe-4918-976c-332f5251a987">are the symbols</span> devel=
opers most often compare by intent</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cdf91effa86d">
<p local-id=3D"da7f1ac1ffee">they are <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker"=
 data-ref=3D"2a506d41-a305-4703-9593-9088a91d4ac7">stable enough </span>for=
 parser-backed extraction</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"303deed8bd51">
<p local-id=3D"018e7ec0be16">they support both "<span class=3D"inline-comme=
nt-marker" data-ref=3D"27635a9d-452f-4a82-a757-0eab425888a5">similar implem=
entation" and "local golden pattern" queries</span></p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"1c5c0d6c575a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Storagedesign"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D=
"5590d0d2-0e7d-4cf1-828c-9d3706551de7">Storage design</span></h2>
<p local-id=3D"8e541f408335">For the MVP, keep the storage model minimal an=
d aligned with the pipeline. <br>
Database notes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"37e535896313">
<li local-id=3D"43cb35103073">
<p local-id=3D"4d9f13ec86b1">f<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-re=
f=3D"e113ac29-028f-47e8-b414-09200076a14e">or symbol semantics, embeddings,=
 and clone edges, we can use Postgres with </span><code><span class=3D"inli=
ne-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"e113ac29-028f-47e8-b414-09200076a14e">pgvect=
or</span></code><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"e113ac29-=
028f-47e8-b414-09200076a14e"> or SQLite with </span><code><span class=3D"in=
line-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"e113ac29-028f-47e8-b414-09200076a14e">sqli=
te-vec</span></code><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"e113a=
c29-028f-47e8-b414-09200076a14e"> for local setup</span></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"68e9a3f90043">
<p local-id=3D"93d774a6abed"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"e113ac29-028f-47e8-b414-09200076a14e">for analytical/event-style worklo=
ads outside this semantic clone pipeline, we can use ClickHouse or DuckDB f=
or local setup</span></p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"037d2a36fd26" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-RecommendedMVPtables:">Recommended MVP tables:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"8b32bc67e854">
<li local-id=3D"b62e2f7c0b67">
<p local-id=3D"dedf03085b22"><code>symbol_semantics</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3564b1e4e03d">
<p local-id=3D"db379b598f04"><code>symbol_features</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0fc6455cfc64">
<p local-id=3D"d90e81cbd83d"><code>symbol_embeddings</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"573f12a06124">
<p local-id=3D"fa73791f9d97"><code>symbol_clone_edges</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"391100cb6128" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Table1:symbol_semantics">Table 1: symbol_semantics</h3>
<p local-id=3D"7dc23982fa03">One row per artefact for the current semantic =
annotation.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"e3fb49c4107a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Suggestedcolumns:"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-re=
f=3D"9aca983e-dec8-4e43-8338-ef2e06255643">Suggested columns</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"6571582c8256">
<li local-id=3D"a19963e22bee">
<p local-id=3D"da6729f4c793">artefact_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"24b58e7e3bfe">
<p local-id=3D"3319d5c19ef1">repo_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"240b7fcba1e2">
<p local-id=3D"5ce0dee0a29f">blob_sha</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e16489b88c1d">
<p local-id=3D"2ed9e6d074ce">summary</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b84bb6b7297">
<p local-id=3D"f48187fcd46d">confidence</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ff38df8485c3">
<p local-id=3D"f15f51bf673a">source_model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"dc204ee046e2">
<p local-id=3D"108550d21b0e">generated_at</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"f9a48e5c0bc4" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Use:">Use:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"4c14b1b2ebf8">
<li local-id=3D"4789738044d5">
<p local-id=3D"677d98549f16">current symbol summary in query responses</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"89f7cd9089bc">
<p local-id=3D"634927b1bf1f"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"9380526d-7a10-4837-aa27-bcccbc89d5cf">provenance</span> and confidence =
display</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"58fa20a560aa" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Table2:symbol_features">Table 2: symbol_features</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ca98e7f10fd0">One row per artefact for the current lexical a=
nd structural retrieval features.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"6502a0b872d9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Suggestedcolumns:.1"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-=
ref=3D"4610580a-f90c-4fa3-ad77-5aac0a55eca3">Suggested columns</span>:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"1e3cfab28de7">
<li local-id=3D"917ca0c11db0">
<p local-id=3D"77b4e3da84c1">artefact_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"37749c55198d">
<p local-id=3D"ea8fd861f636">repo_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b4cba8d27a46">
<p local-id=3D"47b633c6c6ac">blob_sha</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"584d52b61fcb">
<p local-id=3D"6fb1e45d7f18">normalized_name</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"010c3ac62ce7">
<p local-id=3D"953f802a223f">normalized_signature</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"27cc5a615680">
<p local-id=3D"e1cdd9febf7b">identifier_tokens</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e3cd0a9cb7be">
<p local-id=3D"29e7dea0a35b">parent_kind</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ef9670262023">
<p local-id=3D"f3472347ef86">parent_symbol</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"41a4f093aa89">
<p local-id=3D"5b836c1e0983">generated_at</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"aa7d5d629b9d" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Use:.1">Use:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"49f5cb1ba9ad">
<li local-id=3D"10f01e5b0573">
<p local-id=3D"db43ec8f8159">lexical retrieval</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6de504ea4dd7">
<p local-id=3D"c631d47e6595">structural scoring</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1ba5b6d9790d">
<p local-id=3D"60dfdca29928">hybrid reranking in Stage 3</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"04d600a0144d" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Table3:symbol_embeddings"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" =
data-ref=3D"866afd91-7b07-4867-9afb-075f084f6e61">Table 3: symbol_embedding=
s</span></h3>
<p local-id=3D"ed5a45643924">One row per embedding vector.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"5c0a870f5a85" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Suggestedcolumns:.2">Suggested columns:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"fbd3c804f6fb">
<li local-id=3D"e3e04df2155a">
<p local-id=3D"51b3180e18d4">artefact_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2bcedbf7bd68">
<p local-id=3D"61d1dde27a73">repo_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"89f9b381a131">
<p local-id=3D"13b6e6debb14">blob_sha</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"458510e1eda8">
<p local-id=3D"211b0a96e801">model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c290e0962398">
<p local-id=3D"6310d44562d7">embedding vector(...)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ba5abbc52b1e">
<p local-id=3D"4dbd578c82c9">embedding_input_hash</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b7c83eb2816">
<p local-id=3D"85b54e799d8b">generated_at</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"58760074fe0a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Indexes:">Indexes:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"3c257ea25e10">
<li local-id=3D"8804b3e24d2a">
<p local-id=3D"14a299ff99e7">btree (repo_id, artefact_id)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"378a45ed2f8e">
<p local-id=3D"f54ffb131fd0">ivfflat or hnsw on embedding</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"d0ad29095ba8" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Table4:symbol_clone_edges">Table 4: <span class=3D"inline-commen=
t-marker" data-ref=3D"dc5b8bc1-88b6-4b9b-838b-acbf6ef8bd6a">symbol_clone_ed=
ges</span></h3>
<p local-id=3D"905fca2ae08d">Precomputed candidate relationships.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"a78b345e6346" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Suggestedcolumns:.3">Suggested columns:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"009d4ce3640f">
<li local-id=3D"7e5a8f3ec863">
<p local-id=3D"591228b7afd2">repo_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"970be1dc0770">
<p local-id=3D"3baa47c50678">source_artefact_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"af19925c71c6">
<p local-id=3D"337220c188e2">target_artefact_id</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b8b7f88bcc48">
<p local-id=3D"1e140a0d6926">relation_kind</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4411da33e9e8">
<p local-id=3D"42e3b7eb279c">score</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9db3d9426b60">
<p local-id=3D"a3665f1eb15a">lexical_score</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d4ed75244ff4">
<p local-id=3D"6a83b7956de4">structural_score</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1f4f31585107">
<p local-id=3D"d7d1b5ed9d97">semantic_score</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b61cb5a36b08">
<p local-id=3D"a7768f2ef8a2">explanation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7eb0926834d4">
<p local-id=3D"ba276f9c1132">generated_at</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"2ded56e7e224" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Use:.2">Use:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"81b87fbea32e">
<li local-id=3D"a3d851ed0b3a">
<p local-id=3D"ef691733be19"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"1267ad77-074d-4874-aa1d-fbe7846c8687">low-latency query answers</span><=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e0f07ce2379c">
<p local-id=3D"dc7799124961">stable explainability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"873b3e18618c">
<p local-id=3D"f8674d8831d1">offline scoring once, cheap reads many times</=
p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"590f52f6321a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Cloneretrievaldesign"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data=
-ref=3D"37a91df5-db2c-43e5-8e88-afb74b881dd6">Clone retrieval design</span>=
</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3f9ace1e11eb">Use a hybrid score, not embeddings alone.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"bc7a16a751f3" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Retrievalsteps"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"72a03bb9-b7e0-4cc8-bd91-f862f8993334">Retrieval steps</span></h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"633201af3fa8">
<li local-id=3D"0566f1752b13">
<p local-id=3D"c2ce1678a436">Find the query artefact.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7dbf95fc1cf1">
<p local-id=3D"3b870249c15d">Build/query its current embedding.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6113691a0622">
<p local-id=3D"98c3aeb5c4be">Retrieve top-K nearest neighbours inside the s=
ame repo.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"78fcbd8cdf76">
<p local-id=3D"df8948c92fa9">Re-rank using lexical and structural signals.<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4741d75b227f">
<p local-id=3D"aa7d18467255">Label result type and attach explanation.</p><=
/li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"e23a5ac9cb4c" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Scoreformula">Score formula</h3>
<p local-id=3D"2e3274e95b6d"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"f2d84972-1593-4d88-b267-783e8e15d6e0">Recommended first-pass score:</sp=
an></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">final_s=
core =3D
  0.55 * semantic_score +
  0.25 * lexical_score +
  0.20 * structural_score</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"ab684a2ecaad">Where:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b0c82d75b604">
<li local-id=3D"9a544cb0e32e">
<p local-id=3D"44df8db01a63">semantic_score: cosine similarity from pgvecto=
r/sqlite-vec</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"77523504a803">
<p local-id=3D"9e5a794d76c3">lexical_score: token overlap / identifier over=
lap / optional trigram similarity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0e99ee75039b">
<p local-id=3D"94653cdc359d">structural_score: same kind, similar arity, si=
milar control-shape, same framework role, same parent pattern</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"ef6a2d32e7b9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Exactduplicates"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"f2378114-5dda-45e8-bea9-4e4f91ba71a1">Exact duplicates</span></h3>
<p local-id=3D"6b9f1423bd00">Detect separately with deterministic rules:</p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"597735967e76">
<li local-id=3D"397f023678fb">
<p local-id=3D"40931bc7b947">normalized AST hash equal</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"05ae8685c9fd">
<p local-id=3D"0c501ea9b297">normalized body hash equal</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"78838bb8f243">
<p local-id=3D"0d09dbdb2554"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"437946f3-84c9-4746-b060-d047122fc19d">optionally same signature shape</=
span></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"412f21d69de1">Do not rely on embeddings for exact duplicate =
detection.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d9c865bf0f89" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Divergentforks"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"4d3c35ef-4d04-49fd-b042-02c65bb1f54c">Divergent forks</span></h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"b913a657d95f" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Definition:">Definition:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"cc715446fec9">
<li local-id=3D"2044e8c673b8">
<p local-id=3D"9bfa2eaf12b6">two symbols that were formerly very similar, s=
till share name/shape/location ancestry, but now differ meaningfully</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"47dca41f9f4a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Detectionsignal:">Detection signal:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"4cd5a2194472">
<li local-id=3D"173a7a446a51">
<p local-id=3D"c4b5c8338dc8">high lexical/ancestry similarity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b01346cd6ca5">
<p local-id=3D"f5669de6d924">moderate semantic similarity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6288c56f5187">
<p local-id=3D"cf4c0c1dae67">high distance on structural/implementation sha=
pe</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"f036f19f78a9" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Usefulexplanation:">Useful explanation:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"aa3f0a6daec7">
<li local-id=3D"ce67f1c8de36">
<p local-id=3D"4a3794f50174">"same path prefix and signature family, but co=
ntrol flow and callee set have diverged" <br>
Example:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bf2e9c62bf80">
<li local-id=3D"d4216a370c1c">
<p local-id=3D"30e1725ffdec"><code>validateOrderForCheckout</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"768221a6a307">
<p local-id=3D"fcd5fd445a86"><code>validateOrderForDraft</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"dccbc78c37f1" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Goldenpatternsmetrics"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" dat=
a-ref=3D"cb9df86b-f297-4bfa-9cb5-74c52f9d5612">Golden patterns metrics</spa=
n></h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"559f886d1f2a" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Definition:.1">Definition:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"6c8d6b717076">
<li local-id=3D"34c5d8e88c55">
<p local-id=3D"f54fe7b0c7c0">local examples that are similar and look like =
strong design-specific patterns to follow</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"49e0253047fc">For the MVP, this does not need a separate sub=
system.</p>
<p local-id=3D"096fad617229">Treat it as a ranking label on top of clone re=
sults.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"43310e160922" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Simplerankingsignals:">Simple ranking signals:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"b1bf4c31c498">
<li local-id=3D"a6f538b861bd">
<p local-id=3D"43bdae48f9a6">high final similarity score</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4dfab63e7771">
<p local-id=3D"4315f74f10f9">low churn (code does not change often)</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"68606b7c263d">
<p local-id=3D"ef07330621fe">not an exact duplicate</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fedf033845e4">
<p local-id=3D"a103c934a184">stable/mainline code rather than obviously exp=
erimental code</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"81da711b76b6">
<p local-id=3D"90348aeee30b">code health score</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"f1628f73e14d" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Meaning:">Meaning:</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"d6794498a08e">
<li local-id=3D"f9d7ae9d7feb">
<p local-id=3D"f2096f2f22b1">among the similar artefacts, this is a strong =
local example to imitate</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b582649f884f">This is where Bitloops has an advantage: it ca=
n use checkpoint and commit history to rank "good local patterns", not just=
 nearest neighbours.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"47f5c8508952" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Commanddesign">Command design</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"66365245ff05" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Whatinputshouldtheenrichmentcommandtake">What input should <span=
 class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"49818764-cc10-465b-8a62-64d366=
d3a97e">the enrichment command</span> take</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a63f206e39af">Minimum required inputs:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b73455303782">
<li local-id=3D"b83adad7935c">
<p local-id=3D"4568989b6e30">repo_id or implicit current repo</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8fa803bfed38">
<p local-id=3D"3aefff5c3497">target revision: --commit or --ref (same funct=
ion may be different across commits)</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"312d61f70cce" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Userstories"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"7=
fc3413c-a524-48f2-ac7e-d1a7907c82a5">User stories</span></h2>
<p local-id=3D"6f4d316e40a5"><em>(High-level narrative groupings of user in=
tent. Used for understanding context, not implementation tracking.)</em></p=
>
<p local-id=3D"b682d03f1e4a"><strong>US1 - Find similar implementations by =
intent</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to retrieve functions, methods, or modules that solve a similar prob=
lem even when names differ <br><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-r=
ef=3D"e6afa2f5-5d5f-43bb-9418-55c9283d63ee">So that I can reuse local patte=
rns instead of writing bespoke implementations</span></p>
<p local-id=3D"5d1c3dea29db"><strong>US2 - Detect exact duplicates and extr=
action candidates</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want Bitloops to highlight exact duplicates and highly similar copy-paste=
 variants <br><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"9374c1be-5f=
33-451e-962e-557967fa7dd5">So that I can consolidate repeated logic or extr=
act a shared helper</span></p>
<p local-id=3D"38a2c310499d"><strong>US3 - Detect divergent forks of simila=
r logic</strong> <br>
As a <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"23753ea4-3f70-48ce-8=
360-4c635cb5baa4">developer</span> <br>
I want to see when two formerly similar implementations have drifted apart =
<br>
So that I can decide whether the divergence is intentional or a maintenance=
 risk</p>
<p local-id=3D"7c279808f375"><strong>US4 - Prefer strong local patterns</st=
rong> <br>
As an AI agent <br>
I want clone results to surface the most stable and healthy local examples =
first <br>
So that generated changes follow repository conventions</p>
<p local-id=3D"20a345f4e4b7"><strong>US5 - Understand why a match was retur=
ned</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want every clone result to include semantic, lexical, and structural evid=
ence <br>
So that I can trust or reject the recommendation quickly</p>
<p local-id=3D"b54a86c559f2"><strong>US6 - Keep indexing incremental and af=
fordable</strong> <br>
As a platform engineer <br>
I want semantics, embeddings, and clone edges to be recomputed only for cha=
nged symbols and affected neighbours <br>
So that repository indexing stays practical on repeated runs</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"a697a35c5d10" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-BDDscenarios(sourceoftruth)"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marke=
r" data-ref=3D"4ac9ef7d-0af6-4f41-93ea-d3efe63e9666">BDD scenarios (source =
of truth)</span></h2>
<p local-id=3D"ddae5e829d04"><em>(Executable requirements. Every scenario h=
as an ID and maps directly to acceptance criteria.)</em></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"ece48d324e00" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Happypaths">Happy paths</h3>
<p local-id=3D"34d1f8521134"><strong>S1 - Similar implementations are retri=
eved even when names differ</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 repository where `createInvoicePdf` and `renderInvoiceDocument` implement =
the same business intent
And their identifiers and signatures are not lexically identical
And semantic summaries, features, and embeddings have been generated for bo=
th symbols
When a developer asks for semantic clones of `createInvoicePdf`
Then `renderInvoiceDocument` is returned as a clone candidate
And the result has relation_kind `similar_implementation`
And the result includes `semantic_score`, `lexical_score`, `structural_scor=
e`, and a human-readable explanation</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"b0d4d3fd7b92"><strong>S2 - Exact duplicates are classified s=
eparately from semantic neighbours</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo functions whose normalized AST hash and normalized body hash are equal
When clone retrieval runs for either function
Then the other function is returned with relation_kind `exact_duplicate`
And deterministic duplicate detection is used for classification
And embedding similarity alone is not required to label the match as an exa=
ct duplicate</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"d1b960424b80"><strong>S3 - <span class=3D"inline-comment-mar=
ker" data-ref=3D"feeaa4bf-eaf7-410b-85b9-04579895b14f">Extraction candidate=
s</span> are surfaced from repeated local logic</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
hree functions that share a substantial repeated logic fragment with only s=
mall local variations
When clone retrieval and reranking are computed
Then the related functions can be labeled as extraction candidates
And the explanation identifies the shared structure or repeated logic regio=
n</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"762f43e8ce16"><strong>S4 - <span class=3D"inline-comment-mar=
ker" data-ref=3D"0be83184-ce8e-4c10-a797-cfa4611a5feb">Divergent forks are =
identified and explained</span></strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo functions that share a name family, signature shape, and path ancestry
And their control flow or callee set has diverged meaningfully
When clone retrieval runs
Then the pair is labeled with relation_kind `divergent_fork`
And the explanation states that ancestry is similar while implementation be=
havior has diverged</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"e462c27f67c2"><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" =
data-ref=3D"f89d1a66-8edd-45e9-8390-fed58afe37b2">S5 - Golden patterns are =
ranked ahead of weaker neighbours</span></strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given m=
ultiple similar implementations exist for a query symbol
And one candidate has high similarity, low churn, and stronger code health =
than the others
When clone results are ranked
Then that candidate appears ahead of weaker matches
And the result can be labeled as a preferred local pattern</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"699b16e7b4fc" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Edgecases">Edge cases</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e81dc670c1bc"><strong>E1 - Summary generation follows the fa=
llback cascade</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
n important symbol without an existing semantic summary
When Stage 1 semantic enrichment runs
Then the system generates a template summary from stable symbol metadata
And if a valid LLM-generated one-line summary is available it adds that as =
the detail component
And otherwise if a high-confidence docstring or leading comment summary is =
available it adds that as the detail component
And if no valid detail summary is available the final semantic summary rema=
ins the template summary</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"637554bb92bb"><strong>E2 - Incremental indexing reuses uncha=
nged work</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 new repository revision where only one target symbol changed
And unchanged symbols still have the same embedding input hash for the acti=
ve provider and model
When semantic clone enrichment runs for the new revision
Then unchanged symbols reuse their existing semantics and embeddings
And clone edges are recomputed only for changed symbols and their local nei=
ghbourhood</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"77981d33293b" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Errorcases">Error cases</h3>
<p local-id=3D"190ac32d6964"><strong>ERR1 - Missing embedding configuration=
 fails clearly</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given s=
emantic clone enrichment is requested without a valid embedding provider co=
nfiguration
When Stage 2 starts
Then the system returns a clear actionable configuration error
And no partial embedding rows are written for that run</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"fe5cbd26e3d5" id=3D"SemanticClones(SimilarFunctionsandPatte=
rnMatches)-Acceptancecriteria">Acceptance criteria</h2>
<p local-id=3D"d08ebd428998"><em>(Testable conditions that must be satisfie=
d for the feature to be considered complete. Directly derived from BDD scen=
ario IDs.)</em></p>
<ul local-id=3D"b9f31c98358f">
<li local-id=3D"cd05a6713008">
<p local-id=3D"c263cdf0a964">S1 must return semantically similar functions =
or modules even when names differ, and every result must include relation k=
ind, component scores, and explanation text.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aaf95f15f449">
<p local-id=3D"d4424539bc0c">S2 must classify exact duplicates via determin=
istic normalized-hash rules rather than embedding similarity alone.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"173dcf82d764">
<p local-id=3D"e9b7d6ffbfd4">S3 must surface extraction candidates when rep=
eated logic appears with only small local variation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e384b6b58909">
<p local-id=3D"10444a03000d">S4 must classify divergent forks using a combi=
nation of ancestry or lexical similarity and implementation divergence sign=
als.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7ec13de656f2">
<p local-id=3D"143109ce7c68">S5 must rank stable, healthy local examples ab=
ove weaker neighbours and allow them to be identified as preferred local pa=
tterns.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"133cd213175d">
<p local-id=3D"2069c0e3cde5">E1 must generate a final semantic summary for =
every important indexed symbol by always producing a template summary, augm=
enting it with the best available detail summary, preferring a valid LLM-ge=
nerated detail and otherwise using a high-confidence docstring/comment deta=
il, and using the template summary alone when no valid detail summary exist=
s.E2 must skip unnecessary recomputation for unchanged symbols and only ref=
resh clone edges for changed symbols plus affected neighbours.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"81efbbf3f010">
<p local-id=3D"bbb5c5faa2bd">ERR1 must fail with actionable feedback when e=
mbeddings cannot be generated because provider configuration is missing or =
invalid.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9dad4c0a8f40">
<p local-id=3D"6e40cc665569">Every returned clone edge must include <code>r=
elation_kind</code>, <code>score</code>, <code>semantic_score</code>, <code=
>lexical_score</code>, <code>structural_score</code>, and explanation paylo=
ad.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2fedad40ba37">Every BDD scenario has a corresponding accepta=
nce criterion.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
